        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 4:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The addition of the word “common” or “public” perhaps indicates a greater severity of treatment. They were not merely kept in custody, but dealt with as common criminals, compelled to herd with ruffians and robbers and murderers.",
