        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and put them in the common prison",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The noun is the same as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 4:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the notion—that of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ward",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as a place of temporary imprisonment till the formal summoning of the council next day—should here be preserved. Read, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "in public ward",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Such confinement was only precautionary and formed no part of the punishment intended by the Sadducees.",
        "children": []
