  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In the common prison (ἐν τηρήσει δημοσίᾳ)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Incorrect. Τήρησις is not used in the sense of prison, but is an abstract term meaning ward or keeping, as in Acts 4:3. There is no article, moreover. Note, too, that another word is used for the prison in the next verse (τῆς φυλακῆς). Rev., therefore, correctly, in public ward. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Incorrect. Τήρησις is not used in the sense of prison, but is an abstract term meaning ward or keeping, as in ",
            "children": []
